{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017qAtCWuEJti3tw8vXe5DKn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The setup job script reveals the intended \"broken scenario\" - it's not setting up any mirroring policies. The job sets up vhosts, users with intentionally wrong permissions, and queues. There's no mirroring policy in the setup script.\n\nThe note in the task says \"queue mirroring policies on this cluster may have been altered by an external change during this task\". This is a hint that I should check if any mirroring policy is required but currently missing.\n\nIn the context of RabbitMQ classic queues, \"queue mirroring\" refers to the HA policy that mirrors queues across multiple nodes. \n\nFor a 3-node cluster, the typical requirement would be a ha-all or ha-exactly 3 policy, but since the setup job doesn't establish any explicit mirroring policy and no policies currently exist on any vhost, I'm wondering if the \"required policy\" was defined in the scenario but has since been removed. Given that this is a certificate rotation task, the mirroring policy check might be a standard validation step for the case.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1299,"cache_read_input_tokens":47846,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1299},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2a1802f3-d09d-48d3-b09c-7a756ff06a8b","uuid":"3da6a482-b361-408e-9389-ead4168ef4dd","request_id":"req_011CcbpCcyag6kk1kENXsLEs"}
